                            <!--BODY-->
                            <div class="post-body">
                                <h3>Project Details</h3>
                                <p>
                                    Built as an extension of starter kit projects 03 and 05, I wanted to use the motor as a
                                    gauge for ambient temperature. 
                                </p>
        
                                <h3>Reflection on the Project</h3>
                                <p>
                                    First, since temperature sensor was digital and semiconductor (Iâ€™m not too familiar with the theory), 
                                    reversing the direction of the sensor ended up heating up the sensor 
                                    (and possibly damaging the sensor and burning my thumb and finger). <br>
                                    Secondly, if temperature sensor readings were read quickly (every 15 milliseconds), 
                                    then the temperature sensor jumps from ambient to motor load temperature and 
                                    repeats after the temperature sensors read ambient temperature. 
                                    The solution was to increase the delay of the readings so the motor load would not affect the 
                                    temperature readings.
                                </p>       
                            </div>
